comments: I took her online Intro to Psychology. She grades things slowly and didn\'t answer any of my emails. She requires weekly journals but is a little unclear about what they should look like. The class itself was interesting, not too difficult as long as you do the reading. She did give us a week off of the weekly quizzes and discussions which was nice.
Takes weeks to reply to emails and grade assignments.
she was soo easy! easiest class

Awesome teacher! Understands life can get in the way. Tries to eliminate stress by reducing work load. Positive feedback, even though sometimes it was a little bit of a delay. Regardless she was amazing and I\'d recommend her to anyone.
Very easy! I really like it! Easy A! I learned some... I didn\'t read all the chapter. But for a online psy elective it was perfect for me!

Sara Cornell is one of the good professors. She will reach out to assist you. You need only ask. If you don\'t want online, then don\'t sign up for online. She\'s even better in person. Friendly and very informative. But don\'t try to snow her with your research! Do it straight up!

She knows her terms inside and out and has really cute strories. I only wish I had the full experience that I paid for. I was in a 4hr Saturday class which lasted 5 weeks. She didn\'t show to 2 of the classes. This is an easy "A" class but come on! I wish I could get a pay check for showing up to 3/5 classes.
Her online class is set up to run itself, its like she isnt even there.
Dont have this teacher, even if you give your 100%, she will give you a 70%.
Dont take her hibrid class. It blows. Her grading is very harsh.

Sara was one of my favorite teachers. She made everything we did very enjoyable. She is also very flexible, which can be a breath of fresh air compared to other Professors on campus. She is a great instructor, I would most definitely recommend her.

FLEXIBLE was her motto! She was so flexible. Great instructor. She will make sure you understand by giving two or three examples until you get it. If you show up to each class, that\'s 10 points extra credit on the final!

I took a class by her online and didn\'t interact with her much, but the class was not all that hard, especially if you have an interest in Psychology anyway. If I can do it while working and raising a kid and still get an A, I\'d say it\'s a good class to take.
Class was ok! Grading was fairly harsh. If you take this class do not miss a day or you will pay!
